  "prompt": "I am using Quora app. I need to answer the question as anonymous. How to do it?",
  "response": "Okay, here's how to answer anonymously on the Quora app:\n\n1.  **Find the Question:** Navigate to the question you want to answer.\n2.  **Start Your Answer:** Tap on the \"Answer\" button or the \"Write an answer\" field below the question.\n3.  **Answer Anonymously:**\n    *   **Next to your profile picture/name:** Look for an option that says \"Answer Anonymously\". This can appear as a checkbox, a toggle, or a dropdown menu. The exact wording and placement can vary slightly depending on Quora app updates.\n    *   **Tap/Toggle to Enable:** If you see the \"Answer Anonymously\" option, tap the checkbox, or slide the toggle to activate it. It should visibly change to indicate that you are now answering anonymously (e.g., a checkmark appears, the toggle turns green, or the text updates).\n4.  **Write Your Answer:** Compose your answer as usual.\n5.  **Submit Your Answer:** Once you're finished, tap the \"Post\" or \"Submit\" button to publish your anonymous answer.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **No Traceability (Ideally):** When you answer anonymously, your profile will *not* be publicly associated with the answer. Other Quora users will only see \"Anonymous\".\n*   **Quora's Internal Tracking:** Quora still knows who posted the answer. This is for their internal moderation and policy enforcement. Quora reserves the right to reveal your identity if they are legally required to do so, or if you violate their terms of service.\n*   **Moderation:** Anonymous answers are still subject to Quora's moderation policies.\n*   **One-Time Choice:** When you answer, this option is set *once* for that answer. If you change your mind later, you cannot undo the anonymous answer and make it attributable to your profile. The answer is forever anonymous after being posted as such.\n*   **Check Before Posting:** Always double-check that the \"Answer Anonymously\" option is selected *before* you submit your answer. It's easy to forget, and you can't change it later.\n\nIf you have any further questions just ask!\n",
